<font color="#FF0000">DRUGS IN THE BOONIES</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct 16 12:45:31 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I served with A Troop 3/4 Cav, 25th Inf. Div. While drugs <br>
were readily availiable, alcohol was more widely abused <br>
from my experience.There was no drug usage while in the <br>
boonies which is where we were most of the time. If anyone <br>
had been caught smoking pot out there, his shit would have<br>
 been weak indeed.In the boonies you count on everyone to <br>
carry his load. If not, he was out of there. It happened to <br>
several guys. Don't know what happened to them. Don't care!<br>
 When your timecomes to sleep, you needed to know that the <br>
guy on watch is indeed &quot;on watch&quot;.
<p><code>-- ba3425cav  (Reb) </code><p>


